cial limits, and thus not subject to the jurisdiction of its metropolitan municipality. The word metropolitan (municipality) is generally only used as an administrative distinction in Turkey.\nUrban population rate: 73% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nTurkmenistan.\nUrban population rate: 57% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nUnited Arab Emirates.\nDubai-Sharjah-Ajman (DSA) is a metropolitan area in the United Arab Emirates. It consists of the combined, greater urban areas of Dubai, Ajman, and Sharjah. The urban areas at the northeast end of Dubai flow into those of Sharjah, which in turn are contiguous with those of Ajman. The total population is about 5.9 million people as of 2023\nUrban population rate: 87% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nUzbekistan.\nUrban population rate: 44% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nVietnam.\nUrban population rate: 38% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nCentral America and Caribbeans.\nBahamas.\nUrban population rate: 87% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nBarbados.\nUrban population rate: 53% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nCosta Rica.\nUrban population rate: 70% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nCuba.\nUrban population rate: 80% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nDominican Republic.\nUrban population rate: 75% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nEl Salvador.\nUrban population rate: 70% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nGuatemala.\nUrban population rate: 57% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nHaiti.\nUrban population rate: 63% (2024). Metropolitan area population data are referred to 2024.\nHonduras.\nUrban population rate: 59% (2024). Metropolitan area population data